        <tr>
          <td><p><b><font face="Palatino,Book Antiqua"><font color="#008000"><span class="title">Schedule 

        of Conference Activities</span></font></font></b> 

        <p><b><font color="#CC0000">Pre-Conference</font></b> 

                    
      <p>1. Registration
      
<p>Registration is now open through the Conference Web Site. All conference participants 
  must first complete the <a href="../../www.sciforum.net/vc/perl/reg.pl" target="_blank">registration 
  form</a> to be granted a userid and password for access to the conference site 
  and to be added to the conference mailing list. 
<p>2. Abstract Submission&nbsp;

      
<p>Abstracts are now being accepted through the Conference Web Site and should 
  be submitted by <b>February 21st 2002</b>. The abstract should be accompanied 
  by authors' names, institutions, mailing address, phone and fax numbers and 
  email address for correspondence. Authors will be able to indicate which conference 
  section topic their presentation should be presented under. 
<p>3. Acceptance of Abstracts&nbsp;

<p>Conference section conveners will be able to mark acceptance of abstracts

through the Conference Web Site which will be automatically accompanied

by acceptance notification via email to authors. All final acceptance decisions

are to be completed by <b>March 10th 2002</b>. Abstracts will be published through

the Conference Web Site.


<p>4. Conference Paper/Presentation Submission&nbsp;

<p>Papers and Presentations (slideshows) will be accepted through the Conference 
  Web Site and should be received by <b>April 10th 2002</b>. Instructions for format, 
  style and file submission are located on the Conference Web Site. HTML (preferred), 
  .pdf, Word and PowerPoint files will be allowed.&nbsp; 
<p>5. Acceptance of Conference Paper/Presentation&nbsp;

<p>Conference section conveners will be able to mark acceptance of papers and 
  presentations through the Conference Web Site which will be accompanied by acceptance 
  notification via email to authors. Final materials submission and all final 
  acceptance decisions are to be completed by <b>April 20th 2002</b>.&nbsp; 
<p><b><font color="#CC0000">During the Conference</font></b>

<p>The conference will run from <b>May 6th until May 10th 2002</b>. Using the 
  Conference Web Site discussion forum and mailing list, the conference chair 
  will initiate the conference with an overview of the main topics, issues and 
  discussion points to be addressed during the conference. Each topic section 
  convener will post a similar overview of the specific topic covered by their 
  section using the Conference Web Site discussion forum and mailing list.&nbsp; 
<p>1. Viewing Papers/Presentations&nbsp;

<p>During the conference registered users will be able to login to the

Conference Web Site and view all conference papers and presentations.&nbsp;



<p>2. Discussions&nbsp;

<p>Each Conference paper will have an associated Web-based discussion forum.

During the conference registered users will be able to login to the Conference

Web Site and post any comment or reply to the discussion forum area of

any of the conference papers and presentations.&nbsp;

<p>Comments and questions may also be privately posted through the Web

site and relayed directly to authors and any other conference participants.

Chat and instant messaging facilities will also allow real-time exchange

of messages.&nbsp;


<p><b><font color="#CC0000">Post-Conference</font></b>

<p>1. Proceedings Production&nbsp;

<p>After the conference, the collection of conference papers, presentations and 
  any associated discussions will be used to create the conference proceedings. 
  An author may omit any paper, presentation or data from the proceedings at their 
  own request which should be made to and confirmed by MDPI before <b>June 15th 
  2002</b>. The proceedings will be registered with ISSN and published by MDPI 
  in electronic format on CD and the Internet.&nbsp; 
<p>2. Refereed Electronic Journal Publication&nbsp;

<p>There will be a special issue of the peer-refereed electronic journal <i>Entropy</i>, 
  <a href="../../www.mdpi.org/entropy/default.htm" target="_blank">http://www.mdpi.org/entropy/</a>. 
  For this, an editorial committee will be built out of the conference chair, 
  section conveners and other members of the journal's editorial board. All section 
  conveners may put forward selected papers from the conference to the editorial 
  committee who will select referees and communicate the referee reports to the 
  authors. Authors may upload the finally accepted manuscripts to the Conference 
  Web Site; from there, MDPI will automatically process and index manuscripts 
  for publication in the above mentioned special issue of <a href="../../www.mdpi.org/entropy/default.htm" target="_blank"><i>Entropy</i></a>.&nbsp; 
</td>
